'''鬼の岩屋古墳'''、'''鬼ノ岩屋古墳'''、'''鬼の窟古墳'''（おにのいわやこふん）は、[[古墳]]の名称。巨石を使った古墳に対して名づけられることが多い。
* [[鬼の窟古墳 (長崎県壱岐市)]] - 長崎県壱岐市（旧芦辺町）にある古墳。長崎県指定史跡。鬼の岩屋古墳とも表記。 * [[高下古墳]] - 長崎県雲仙市（旧国見町）にある古墳。長崎県指定史跡。鬼の岩屋古墳とも言う。 * [[鬼の岩屋古墳 (熊本県)]] - 熊本県八代市にある古墳。八代市指定史跡。 * [[鬼ノ岩屋古墳]] - 大分県別府市にある古墳。国指定史跡。鬼の岩屋古墳とも表記。 * 鬼の窟古墳 - 宮崎県西都市の[[西都原古墳群]]中の古墳。西都原古墳群は国指定特別史跡。鬼の岩屋古墳とも表記。
{{aimai}}

'''Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun''' (鬼の岩屋古墳), also known as '''Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun''' or '''Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun''' (鬼ノ岩屋古墳, 鬼の窟古墳, おにのいわやこふん), is a name given to [[kofun]] (ancient Kofuns). This name is often used for kofun constructed using large stones, like a demon moved them, hence the name Demon Stone or [[:en:Oni|Oni]] no Iwa
* {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Iki City)|ja|鬼の窟古墳 (壱岐市)}} - Located in Iki City (formerly Ashibe Town), Nagasaki Prefecture. A Nagasaki Prefecture-designated historic site. Also referred to as "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Takage Kofun|ja|高下古墳}} - Located in Unzen City (formerly Kunimi Town), Nagasaki Prefecture. A Nagasaki Prefecture-designated historic site. Also called "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Kumamoto City)|ja|鬼のいわや古墳}} - Located in Kita Ward, Kumamoto City (formerly Ueki Town), Kumamoto Prefecture. A former Ueki Town-designated historic site. * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Yatsushiro)|ja|鬼の岩屋古墳 (熊本県八代市)}} - Located in Yatsushiro City, Kumamoto Prefecture. A Yatsushiro City-designated historic site. * {{ill|Oni-no-iwa Kofun|lt=Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Beppu)|ja|鬼ノ岩屋古墳 (別府市)|1=Oni-no-iwa Kofun}} - Located in Beppu City, Ōita Prefecture. A National Historic Site. Also referred to as "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Saito)|ja|鬼の窟古墳 (西都市)}} - Located within the {{ill|Saitobaru Kofun Group|ja|西都原古墳群}} in Saito City, Miyazaki Prefecture. The Saitobaru Kofun Group is designated as a Special Historic Site of Japan. Also referred to as "Saitobaru No. 206 Kofun" or "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun."
{{aimai}}
