* {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Iki City)|ja|鬼の窟古墳 (壱岐市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Iki City)|qq=}} - Located in Iki City (formerly Ashibe Town), Nagasaki Prefecture. A Nagasaki Prefecture-designated historic site. Also referred to as "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Takage Kofun|ja|高下古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takage Kofun|qq=}} - Located in Unzen City (formerly Kunimi Town), Nagasaki Prefecture. A Nagasaki Prefecture-designated historic site. Also called "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Kumamoto City)|ja|鬼のいわや古墳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Kumamoto City)|qq=}} - Located in Kita Ward, Kumamoto City (formerly Ueki Town), Kumamoto Prefecture. A former Ueki Town-designated historic site. * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Yatsushiro)|ja|鬼の岩屋古墳 (熊本県八代市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Yatsushiro)|qq=}} - Located in Yatsushiro City, Kumamoto Prefecture. A Yatsushiro City-designated historic site. * {{ill|Oni-no-iwa Kofun|lt=Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Beppu)|ja|鬼ノ岩屋古墳 (別府市)|1=Oni-no-iwa Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-iwa Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-iwa Kofun|qq=}} - Located in Beppu City, Ōita Prefecture. A National Historic Site. Also referred to as "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun." * {{ill|Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Saito)|ja|鬼の窟古墳 (西都市)|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun (Saito)|qq=}} - Located within the {{ill|Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|lt=Saitobaru Kofun Cluster|lt=Saitobaru Kofun Group|ja|西都原古墳群|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saitobaru Kofun Group|qq=}} in Saito City, Miyazaki Prefecture. The Saitobaru Kofun Group is designated as a Special Historic Site of Japan. Also referred to as "Saitobaru No. 206 Kofun" or "Oni-no-Iwaya Kofun."
